election_record.label: Connecticut 1821 State Senate

overview.note: Nathaniel Smith received 78 votes as Nathan Smith.
Samuel A. Foot received 7 votes as Samuel Foote and 1 vote as Samuel R. Foot.
John S. Peters received 2 votes as John Peters and 4 votes as John T. Peters.
David Hill received 11 votes as David Hall and 1 vote as David Hale.
David Boardman received 5 votes as David S. Boardman.
David Plant received 4 votes as David Platt.
Dixon Hall received 1 vote as Dikan Hall.
Jonathan W. Edwards received 18 votes as John W. Edwards and 1 vote as Jonathan Edwards.
Noah B. Benedict received 9 votes as Noah Benedict.
Roger M. Sherman received 3 votes as Roger M. Sherwood.
Asa Bacon received 38 votes as Asa Bacon, Jr.
Ebenezer Stoddard received 1 vote as Ebenezer S. Stoddard.
Thomas S. Williams received 1 vote as Thomas W. Williams.
William M. Betts received 1 vote as William Betts.
A. S. and Gideon T. are listed as candidates with unknown number of votes.
One unknown candidate received an unknown number of votes.
